Project License Notice
======================

This repository contains:
1) Build/tooling code in this repository (scripts, Makefile, styles, plist metadata).
2) Dictionary source data obtained from an external provider (ISLEX).

The legal terms for (2) are not overridden by this repository.

Data License Summary (Important)
--------------------------------
The lexical data pipeline depends on ISLEX (2026-02 release), the
Icelandic-Scandinavian multilingual dictionary distributed under Creative
Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0) by Stofnun
Árna Magnússonar í íslenskum fræðum / CLARIN Iceland.

Under CC BY-SA 4.0, you may copy, redistribute, and adapt the data —
including in the form of a compiled dictionary bundle — provided you:
- give appropriate attribution (see CREDITS.md for exactly who/what to credit), and
- distribute any such derivative under this same CC BY-SA 4.0 license.

Practical compliance guidance:
- Allowed: local/private building and personal usage with attribution.
- Allowed: redistributing compiled .dictionary bundles, with attribution,
  under CC BY-SA 4.0.
- Allowed: commercial use (CC BY-SA 4.0 has no NonCommercial restriction).
- Not allowed: redistributing this data, or derivatives of it, under a more
  restrictive license than CC BY-SA 4.0, or without attribution.

This repository currently still ships build tooling only (no compiled
.dictionary bundles or source data checked in) — that is a project choice
for now, not a legal requirement under this license. See README.md's
"Release Assets Policy" for current status.

Note: an earlier version of this project built from the ISLEX 2023-12
release, which was CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 (no redistribution, non-commercial only).
This project has since migrated to the 2026-02 release; if you are building
from a different ISLEX release than 2026-02, verify its license directly —
do not assume it matches this notice.

You are responsible for verifying current terms at the original data source.
If source licensing changes, update this notice and your distribution behavior.

